				</section>
				<section>
					<h3>Conclusions</h3>
					<p>
						<ul>
							<li>We have reported a simple modification to the unilateral approach to the spine.</li>
							<li>This technique provides a wider lateral space, allowing for improved viewing angles and easier insertion of instruments.</li>
							<li>Minimal damage was observed to the paravertebral muscles.</li>
							<li>This technique proves to be beneficial for removing spinal tumors located ventrally.</li>
						</ul>
					</p>
					<p class="ref">Chang HS, et al. Modified unilateral approach for ventrally located spinal tumors. <i>Neurol Med Chir</i> in press</p>
